	pageEncoding="UTF-8"%>

<div class="row">
	<div class="col-md-6">
		<div class="recipe-modal-img-container">
			<img src="${pageContext.request.contextPath}/recipes/Zucchini_Lasagna.jpg" />
		</div>
		<h4>Ingredients</h4>
		<ul class="ingredients">
			<li>1 pound ground beef</li>
			<li>1 cup green bell peppers, chopped</li>
			<li>1/2 cup green onions, chopped</li>
			<li>1 Tbsp fresh basil</li>
			<li>1 Tbsp parsley</li>
			<li>1 Tbsp oregano</li>
			<li>1 zucchini, sliced thinly (broccoli slaw works great too, slightly steamed)</li>
			<li>1 1/4 cups mushrooms, sliced</li>
			<li>15 ounce can tomato sauce</li>
			<li>3 cloves garlic, minced</li>
			<li>6 ounces tomato paste</li>
			<li>salt and pepper to taste</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
	<div class="col-md-6">
		<h4>Instructions</h4>
		<ol class="instructions">
			<li>brown the ground beef in a large pot over medium heat, stirring frequently. Add garlic, onion, and green pepper and saute for 5 minutes.</li>
			<li>Stir in tomato paste and sauce</li>
			<li>Add parsley, basil, oregano, salt, and pepper</li>
			<li>Bring sauce to a light boil and remove from heat</li>
			<li>Place a thin layer of sauce in a 9x13" baking dish</li>
			<li>Layer zucchini and mushrooms over sauce. repeat, alternating layers of sauce, then zucchini and mushrooms.</li>
			<li>Bake lasagna at 325F for 15 minutes, covered with foil. Remove foil and increase temperature to 350F and bake an additional 15 minutes.</li>
		</ol>
		<div class="help-text">Note: the zucchini and mushrooms will release water upon cooking ...  with that in mind, the sauce for this recipe is thicker than would be expected</div>
	</div>
</div>